</head>
<body onload="initMap()">
    <div id="map"></div>
</body>
</html>
```

### Notes:
- Replace `"YOUR_API_KEY"` with your actual Google Maps API key.
- The code above initializes a simple map centered on San Francisco.
- To "time travel," you would need to manage your own imagery data and potentially tie it to user interactions with the map.
- For any detailed image data from Google Maps or Earth, you would typically rely on the platform's built-in features rather than API endpoints.

